history.content: Unless you cancel the swap, you'd still get auto swapped if there's an open seat in 126 after class starts. Make sure to cancel the swap if you don't want to drop 161

Hi, I am currently enrolled in 161, but I have a swap request with it for 126, which I am currently waitlist position 27 for. I heard 126 already expanded this semester, so it is most likely that I would only be able to get off the waitlist when the semester starts and people drop. In that case, do I have to just stick it through for the first few weeks of the semester and do work for both classes in hopes that I get off the waitlist?
history.subject: What happens when the semester stars and a swap still hasnt gone through
